{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-awesome-all-timeline-js","path":"/2016/12/30/","result":{"data":{"site":{"siteMetadata":{"title":"Track Awesome List"}},"allAwesomeItem":{"nodes":[{"awesomeListRepo":"passy/awesome-recursion-schemes","categoryHTML":"<h2>Papers</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://research.microsoft.com/en-us/um/people/simonpj/Papers/hmap/hmap.ps\">Scrap your boilerplate: a practical design pattern for generic programming, 2003, SPJ et al.</a> -\nDesign pattern for writing programs that traverse data structures built from rich mutually-recursive data types.</li>","updatedAt":"2016-12-30T22:37:25.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"passy/awesome-recursion-schemes","categoryHTML":"<h2>Papers</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://maartenfokkinga.github.io/utwente/mmf91m.pdf\">Functional Programming with Bananas, Lenses, Envelopes and Barbed Wire, 1991, Meijer et al.</a> -\nThe original paper most of this is based on.</li>","updatedAt":"2016-12-30T22:35:55.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"passy/awesome-recursion-schemes","categoryHTML":"<h2>Introductions</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://jtobin.io/practical-recursion-schemes\">Practical Recursion Schemes</a> -\nIntroduction to pattern functors, fix points, anamorphisms, catamorphisms,\nparamorphisms and hylomorphisms, requiring very little prior knowledge.</li>","updatedAt":"2016-12-30T22:30:02.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"passy/awesome-recursion-schemes","categoryHTML":"<h2>Introductions</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://blog.sumtypeofway.com/an-introduction-to-recursion-schemes/\">An Introduction to Recursion Schemes</a> -\nThree-part series in which you discover recursion schemes from scratch and\nimplement a small subset of Edward Kmett's library.</li>","updatedAt":"2016-12-30T22:30:02.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"passy/awesome-recursion-schemes","categoryHTML":"<h2>Introductions</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.schoolofhaskell.com/user/bartosz/understanding-algebras\">Understanding Algebras</a> -\nBartosz Milewski explains F-algebras and shows how to use them in the context of\ncatamorphisms.</li>","updatedAt":"2016-12-30T22:30:02.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"passy/awesome-recursion-schemes","categoryHTML":"<h2>Articles</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://wiki.haskell.org/Catamorphisms\">Catamorphisms</a> - Definition on the Haskell Wiki.</li>","updatedAt":"2016-12-30T22:30:02.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"passy/awesome-recursion-schemes","categoryHTML":"<h2>Articles</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.schoolofhaskell.com/user/edwardk/recursion-schemes/catamorphisms\">Catamorphisms</a> -\nShort definition with code on School of Haskell by Edward Kmett.</li>","updatedAt":"2016-12-30T22:30:02.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"passy/awesome-recursion-schemes","categoryHTML":"<h2>Papers</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://www.cs.ox.ac.uk/ralf.hinze/publications/Sorting.pdf\">A Duality of Sorts, 2013, Hinze et al.</a> -\nShows that many basic sorting algorithms exist as a pair, and that these pairs\narise naturally out of the duality between folds and unfolds.</li>","updatedAt":"2016-12-30T22:30:02.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"passy/awesome-recursion-schemes","categoryHTML":"<h2>Papers</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://www.cs.ox.ac.uk/people/daniel.james/sorting/sorting.pdf\">Sorting with Bialgebras and Distributive Laws, 2012, Hinze et al.</a> -\nShows how paramorphisms and apomorphisms can be used for more efficient\nimplementations of sorting algorithms.</li>","updatedAt":"2016-12-30T22:30:02.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"passy/awesome-recursion-schemes","categoryHTML":"<h2>Presentations</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://www.timphilipwilliams.com/slides.html\">Slidedecks by Tim Philip Williams</a> -\n\"Recursion Schemes by Example\" and \"Exotic Tools for Exotic Trades\" provide\nconcise definitions as well as practical examples of many recursion schemes.</li>","updatedAt":"2016-12-30T22:30:02.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"passy/awesome-recursion-schemes","categoryHTML":"<h2>Presentations</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=9EGYSb9vov8\">Unifying Structured Recursion Schemes</a> -\n12 min presentation by Ralf Hinze, Nicolas Wu, and Jeremy Gibbons.</li>","updatedAt":"2016-12-30T22:30:02.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"passy/awesome-recursion-schemes","categoryHTML":"<h2>Presentations</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Zw9KeP3OzpU\">Recursion Schemes</a> -\nPresented by Tim Williams at the London Haskell meetup.</li>","updatedAt":"2016-12-30T22:30:02.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"passy/awesome-recursion-schemes","categoryHTML":"<h2>Presentations</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=PK4SOaAGVfg\">F-algebras or: How I Learned to Stop Worrying and Love the Type System</a> -\nPresented by Anthony Burzillo at the NYC Haskell User's Group.</li>","updatedAt":"2016-12-30T22:30:02.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"passy/awesome-recursion-schemes","categoryHTML":"<h2>Presentations</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=i5A2Amfcir8\">A Gentle Introduction to Recursion Schemes</a> -\nPresented by Jean Remi Desjardins at Lambdaconf 2016.</li>","updatedAt":"2016-12-30T22:30:02.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"passy/awesome-recursion-schemes","categoryHTML":"<h2>Implementations</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/ekmett/recursion-schemes/\">recursion-schemes</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/ekmett/recursion-schemes/\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">270</spa